    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin discs</p><p>Add the <strong>potato</strong> <strong>discs</strong> to a large baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-thigh-and-mushroom-hot-pot-with-kale/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Whilst the potatoes are cooking, peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> (no need to peel!)</p><p>Cut your<strong> baby button mushrooms</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-thigh-and-mushroom-hot-pot-with-kale/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-thigh-and-mushroom-hot-pot-with-kale/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>soft cheese </strong>and <strong>dried oregano</strong> in 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml] </span><strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong> and shake off any excess water</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-thigh-and-mushroom-hot-pot-with-kale/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is beginning to brown, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>carrot </strong>and<strong> mushrooms </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 3-4 min or until lightly golden and beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-thigh-and-mushroom-hot-pot-with-kale/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>creamy stock </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook over a medium heat for 4-5 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your<strong> chicken mix</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>chicken mix </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>(Tip: Use individual dishes for fancy presentation!)</p><p>Top with the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>potato</strong> <strong>slices</strong> and put in the oven for 15-20 min or until the potatoes are golden, the hotpot is bubbling and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy chicken & mushroom hot pot</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-thigh-and-mushroom-hot-pot-with-kale/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>When the hotpot is nearly ready, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted add your <strong>shredded kale</strong> with a small splash of <strong>cold water </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until bright green and wilted</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-thigh-and-mushroom-hot-pot-with-kale/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy chicken & mushroom hot pot</strong> with the <strong>kale</strong> to the side</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
